[normal]Some farmers only grow one crop because 
[normal]th
[normal]e
[normal] produce from that crop is fed to their livestock
[normal] (poultry farmers)
[normal].  They will now have to grow three crops, two will have to be sold and taken off farm by lorry and feed bought to replace the loss of produce
[normal], this will have to be
[normal] brought onto the farm
[normal] by lorry – more CO
[normal]2
[normal] emissions.  No benefit there to the environment
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Some farmers grow two crops because that is what their land is suited to and fits in with their farming system
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-      Others farmers, usually large farmers, will have no difficulty in g
[normal]rowing three or more 
[normal]       crops.  It may be that more than one crop is fed to their livestock (dairy farmers) with  the other crops sold off farm
[normal]&#xa0;
